abstract: Emirates says it will add Orlando as 10th United States daily service destination from Dubai in 2015; announcement comes even as US airline companies have been lobbying Obama administration to limit new flight offerings from Emirates, Etihad Airways and Qatar Airways.
lead_paragraph: The new daily service from Dubai will begin Sept. 1 as U.S. airlines are pushing to freeze new flights from the three Persian Gulf giants.

headline.main: Emirates Has Plans to Make Orlando Its 10th U.S. Destination
headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; Emirates to Begin Flying to Orlando in September
